  "prompt": "If I don't clear the ASAT, will I not be able to get into the ALLEN Career Institute?",
  "response": "To gain admission to the ALLEN Career Institute, specifically for their programs related to competitive exams, it is often necessary to clear the ASAT (Allen Scholarship Admission Test). The ASAT typically serves as a way for the institute to evaluate prospective students' academic skills and readiness for their courses.\n\nIf you do not clear the ASAT, it may affect your chances of being accepted into their programs, as many coaching institutes use such assessments to rank candidates and offer admissions based on their performance. However, it's best to check directly with the ALLEN Career Institute's official website or contact their admissions office for the most accurate and detailed information regarding their admission criteria and any alternative options that may be available.",
